MktRt.description: Used only for credit index trade. This contains the credit spread ("fair value") at which the trade was executed. The market rate varies over the life of the index depending on market conditions. This is the price of the index as quoted by trading desks.

DelayInd.description:
Applicable to credit default swaps on mortgage backed securities to specify whether payment delays are applicable to the fixed amount. 
                    Residential mortgage backed securities typically have a payment delay of 5 days between the coupon date of the reference obligation and the payment date of the synthetic swap. 
                    Commercial mortage backed securities do not typically have a payment delay, with both payment dates (the coupon date of the reference obligation and the payment date of the synthetic swap) being on the 25th of each month.

CshSettlInd.description: Indicates whether cash settlement is applicable.

SettlCcy.description: Specifies the currency that the stream settles in (to support swaps that settle in a currency different from the notional currency). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

OtherDayCnt.description: The industry name of the day count convention not listed in LegPaymentStreamDayCount(40283).

AcrlDays.description: The number of days from the adjusted calculation period start date to the adjusted value date, calculated in accordance with the applicable day count fraction.

Disc.description: Discount rate. The rate is expressed in decimal, e.g. 5% is expressed as 0.05.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

CmpndgXIDRef.description: Reference to the stream which details the compounding fixed or floating rate.

CmpndgSpread.description: The spread to be used for compounding. Used in scenarios where the interest payment is based on a compounding formula that uses a compounding spread in addition to the regular spread.

InitPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there is an initial exchange of principal on the effective date.

IntrmPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there are intermediate or interim exchanges of principal during the term of the swap.

FnlPrncplExchInd.description: Indicates whether there is a final exchange of principal on the termination date.

FlatRtInd.description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', the Flat Rate is the New Worldwide Tanker Nominal Freight Scale for the Freight Index Route taken at the trade date of the transaction "Fixed". If 'N' it is taken on each pricing date "Floating".

FlatRtAmt.description: Specifies the actual monetary value of the flat rate when LegPaymentStreamFlatRateIndicator(41549) = 'Y'.

FlatRtCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the actual flat rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

MaxPmtAmt.description: Specifies the limit on the total payment amount.

MaxPmtCcy.description: Specifies the currency of total payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

MaxTxnAmt.description: Specifies the limit on the payment amount that goes out in any particular calculation period.

MaxTxnCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the period payment amount limit. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CmpndgFixedRt.description: The compounding fixed rate applicable to the payment stream.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of payments.

LastReglrDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last regular payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when payment dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative payment date offset.

MADts.description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that payment dates are specified in the relevant master agreement.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's payment date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadjusted fixed stream payment date.

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted final price payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the final price payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative final price payment date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted final price payment date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the reset dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    If the reset frequency is specified as daily this element must not be included. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for frequency of resets.

InitReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the initial fixing date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

InitPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative initial fixing date offset.

FixngReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the fixing date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FixngPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative fixing date offset.

Dt.description: The fixing date. Type of date is specified in LegPaymentStreamFixingDateType(42461).

CutoffPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative rate cut-off date offset.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's reset date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's initial fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Rt.description: The rate applicable to the fixed rate payment stream.

Amt.description: The leg instrument payment stream's fixed payment amount. In a CDS, this can be an alternative to LegPaymentStreamRate(40326).

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency in which LegPaymentStreamFixedAmount(40327) or LegPaymentStreamRate(40326) is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

FixedAmt.description: Specifies the total fixed payment amount.

FutValNotl.description: The future value notional is normally only required for certain non-deliverable interest rate swaps (e.g. Brazillian Real (BRL) vs. CETIP Interbank Deposit Rate (CDI)). The value is calculated as follows: Future Value Notional = Notional Amount * (1 + Fixed Rate) ^ (Fixed Rate Day Count Fraction). The currency is the same as the stream notional.

FutValDt.description: The adjusted value date of the future value amount.

WorldScaleRt.description: The number of Worldscale points for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a wet voyage charter commodity swap.

CtrctPx.description: The price per relevant unit for purposes of the calculation of a fixed amount for a dry voyage charter or time charter commodity swap.

CtrctPxCcy.description: Specifies the currency of LegPaymentStreamContractPrice(41559). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Ndx.description: The payment stream floating rate index.

NdxID.description: Security identifier of the floating rate index.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the payment stream's floating rate index curve period.

Ndx2.description: The payment stream's second floating rate index.

Ndx2ID.description: Security identifier of the second floating rate index.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Ndx2Period.description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the payment stream's floating rate index curve.

NdxLctn.description: Specifies the location of the floating rate index.

NdxLvl.description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD index level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

RefLvl.description: This is the weather Cooling Degree Days (CDD), Heating Degree Days (HDD) or HDD reference level specified as the number of (amount of) weather index units specified by the parties in the related confirmation.

RefLvlZero.description: When set to 'Y', it indicates that the weather reference level equals zero.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Spread.description: The basis points spread from the index specified in LegPaymentStreamRateIndex(40331).

SpreadCcy.description: Specifies the currency of the floating rate spread. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

RtFctr.description: The number to be multiplied by the derived floating rate of the leg's payment stream in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the floating rate conversion factor is 1.

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

InitRt.description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

LastResetRt.description: The floating rate determined at the most recent reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

FnlRt.description: The floating rate determined at the final reset. The rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as 0.05.

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

CalcLagPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the calculation lag duration.

FirstObsvtnDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted initial price observation date.

FirstObsvtnReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the initial price observation date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FirstObsvtnOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.

FirstObsvtnDt.description: The adjusted initial price observation date.

PxngDayCnt.description: The number of days over which pricing should take place.

PxngClndr.description:
Specifies the business calendar to use for pricing. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-business-calendar for values.

LagPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the inflation lag period. The lag period is the offsetting period from the payment date which determineds the reference period for which the inflation index is observed.

PublctnSrc.description: The publication source, such as relevant web site, news publication or a government body, where inflation information is obtained.

InitLvl.description: Initial known index level for the first calculation period.

FallbckBond.description: Indicates whether a fallback bond as defined in the 2006 ISDA Inflation Derivatives Definitions, sections 1.3 and 1.8, is applicable or not. If not specified, the default value is "Y" (True/Yes).

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

RtnRtNotlReset.description: Indicates whether the term "Equity Notional Reset" as defined in the ISDA 2002 Equity Derivatives Definitions is applicable ("Y") or not.

LinkInitLvl.description: Price level at which the correlation or variance swap contract will strike.

LinkFClsngLvl.description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the closing level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

LinkExpngLvl.description: Indicates whether the correlation or variance swap contract will ("Y") strike off the expiring level of the default exchange traded contract or not.

LinkEstTrdgDays.description: The expected number of trading days in the variance or correlation swap stream.

LinkStrkPx.description: The strike price of a correlation or variance swap stream.

LinkMaxBndry.description:
Specifies the maximum or upper boundary for variance or strike determination. 
                    For a variation swap stream all observations above this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. 
                    For a correlation swap stream the maximum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

LinkMinBndry.description:
Specifies the minimum or lower boundary for variance or strike determination. 
                    For a variation swap stream all observations below this price level will be excluded from the variance calculation. 
                    For a correlation swap stream the minimum boundary is a percentage of the strike price.

LinkNumDataSeries.description: Number of data series for a correlation swap. Normal market practice is that correlation data sets are drawn from geographic market areas, such as America, Europe and Asia Pacific. Each of these geographic areas will have its own data series to avoid contagion.

VarncCap.description: Indicates the scaling factor to be multiplied by the variance strike price thereby making variance cap applicable.

DaysAdjmt.description: Indicates whether the contract specifies that the notional should be scaled by the number of days in range divided by the estimate trading days or not. The number of "days in range" refers to the number of returns that contribute to the realized volatility.

ExchCtrctRefID.description: References a contract listed on an exchange through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

VegaNotlAmt.description: Vega Notional represents the approximate gain/loss at maturity for a 1% difference between RVol (realized volatility) and KVol (strike volatility). It does not necessarily represent the Vega risk of the trade.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the pricing dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

DayNum.description: The occurrence of the day of week on which pricing takes place.

Dt.description: The adjusted or unadusted fixed stream pricing date.

Ccy.description: The currency in which the formula amount is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CcyDtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method according to which the formula amount currency is determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

RefAmt.description:
Specifies the reference amount when this term either corresponds to the standard ISDA Definition (either the 2002 Equity Definition for the Equity Amount, or the 2000 Definition for the Interest Amount), or refers to a term defined elsewhere in the swap document. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Payment_Amount_Relative_To for code list of reference amounts.

FrmlaLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) LegPaymentStreamFormula(42486) field.

Frmla.description: Contains an XML representation of the formula. Defined for flexibility in choice of language (MathML, OpenMath or text).

Desc.description: A description of the math formula in LegPaymentStreamFormula(42486).

FrmlaImgLen.description: Length in bytes of the LegPaymentStreamFormulaImage(42452) field.

FrmlaImg.description: Image of the formula image when represented through an encoded clip in base64Binary.

RnvstmntInd.description: Indicates whether the dividend will be reinvested.

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

ExtrordCcy.description: The currency in which the excess dividend is denominated. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

ExtrordDtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method in which the excess amount is determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

AcrlFixedRt.description:
The dividend accrual fixed rate per annum expressed as a decimal. 
                    A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

NumNdxUnits.description: The number of index units applicable to dividends.

CshPctage.description:
Declared cash dividend percentage. 
                    A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

CshEqvlntPctage.description:
Declared cash-equivalent dividend percentage. 
                    A value of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

SpeclDividendInd.description: Indicates whether special dividends are applicable.

MtrlDividendInd.description: Indicates whether material non-cash dividends are applicable.

ExchDividendInd.description: Indicates whether option exchange dividends are applicable.

AddtnlDividendInd.description: Indicates whether additional dividends are applicable.

AllDividendInd.description: Represents the European Master Confirmation value of 'All Dividends' which, when applicable, signifies that, for a given Ex-Date, the daily observed share price for that day is adjusted (reduced) by the cash dividend and/or the cash value of any non-cash dividend per share (including extraordinary dividends) declared by the issuer.

Seq.description: Defines the ordinal dividend period. E.g. 1 = First period, 2 = Second period, etc.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will begin.

EndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on which the dividend period will end.

UndlrRefID.description: References the dividend underlier through the instrument's UnderlyingSecurityID(309) which must be fully specified in an instance of the UnderlyingInstrument component.

StrkPx.description: Specifies the fixed strike price of the dividend period.

ValDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted dividend period valuation date.

ValDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period valuation date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

ValDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period valuation date offset.

ValDt.description: The adjusted dividend period valuation date.

PmtDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted dividend period payment date.

PmtDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the dividend period payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

PmtDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative dividend period payment date offset.

PmtDt.description: The adjusted dividend period payment date.

XID.description: Identifier for linking this stream dividend period to an underlier through an instance of RelatedInstrumentGrp.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend period date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the FX trigger date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative FX trigger date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted FX trigger date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's FX trigger date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ndx.description: The dividend accrual floating rate index.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the dividend accrual floating rate index curve.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the contract.

Spread.description: The basis points spread from the index specified in LegDividendFloatingRateIndex(42312).

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. It is only required where the floating rate is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

InitRt.description: The initial floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. This is assumed to be the first required reset rate for the first regular calculation period. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the rounding precision of the final rate in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the accrual payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative accrual payment date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted accrual payment date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the instrument's dividend accrual payment date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

CommCcy.description: Specifies the currency the commission amount is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

DtrmnMeth.description:
Specifies the method by which the underlier prices are determined. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/determination-method for values.

AmtReltv.description:
Specifies the reference amount when the return rate amount is relative to another amount in the trade. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Amount_Relative_To for code list of relative amounts.

QteTyp.description:
Specifies the type of the measure applied to the return rate's asset, e.g. valuation, sensitivity risk. This could be an NPV, a cash flow, a clean price, etc. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/asset-measure for values.

QteUnit.description:
Specifies the units that the measure is expressed in. If not specified, the default is a price/value in currency units. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/price-quote-units for values.

QteCcy.description: Specifies the currency the return rate quote is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

QteCcyTyp.description:
Specifies the type of currency, e.g. settlement currency, base currency, etc., that the quote is reported in. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/reporting-currency-type for values.

QteTm.description: The time when the quote is to be generated.

QteDt.description: The date when the quote is to be generated.

QteExpTm.description: The time when the quote ceases to be valid.

QteBizCtr.description:
The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with LegReturnRateQuoteTimeType(42547) or LegReturnRateQuoteTime(42548) and LegReturnRateQuoteDate(42549), e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

QteExch.description: Specifies the exchange (e.g. stock or listed futures/options exchange) from which the quote is obtained.

QteModel.description:
Specifies the pricing model used to evaluate the underlying asset price. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/pricing-model for values.

CshFlow.description:
Specifies the type of cash flows, e.g. coupon payment, premium fee, settlement fee, etc. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/cashflow-type for values.

ValTm.description: The time at which the calculation agent values the underlying asset.

ValTmBizCtr.description:
The business center calendar used for adjustments associated with LegReturnRateValuationTimeType(42555) or LegReturnRateValuationTime(42556), e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Px.description: Specifies the price of the underlying swap asset.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency of the price of the leg swap asset. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

CcySym.description: Specifies the currency pair for the FX conversion expressed using the CCY1/CCY2 convention. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

FxRt.description: The rate of exchange between the two currencies specified in LegReturnRateFXCurrencySymbol(42531).

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. 
                    For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate. 
                    When LegReturnRateInformationSource(42561) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. 
                    See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option.

RefHdng.description: Identifies the page heading from the rate source.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation date offset.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

StartDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

StartDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation start date offset.

StartDt.description: The adjusted start date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

EndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

EndDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the return rate valuation end date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

EndDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative return rate valuation end date offset.

EndDt.description: The adjusted end date for return rate valuation. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which return rate valuation dates occur.

Dt.description: The return rate valuation date. The type of date is specified in LegReturnRateValuationDateType(42573).

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the return rate valuation unadjusted or relative dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ndx.description: The payment stream's compounding floating rate index.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the payment stream's compounding floating rate index curve period.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the compounding floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Spread.description: The basis points spread from the index specified in LegPaymentStreamCompoundingRateIndex(42427).

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. It is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the compounding floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the compounding floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate. The rate is expressed as a decimal, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

InitRt.description: The initial compounding floating rate reset agreed between the principal parties involved in the trade. It should only be included when the rate is not equal to the rate published on the source implied by the floating rate index. The initial rate is expressed in decimal form, e.g. 5% is represented as "0.05".

FnlRtPrcsn.description: Specifies the compounding floating rate rounding precision in terms of a number of decimal places. Note how a percentage rate rounding of 5 decimal places is expressed as a rounding precision of 7.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the compounding dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding date offset.

Skip.description: The number of periods in the "RelativeTo" schedule that are between each date in the compounding schedule. A skip of 2 would mean that compounding dates are relative to every second date in the "RelativeTo" schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency at which compounding dates occur.

FirstDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

LastDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last date of the compounding schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of dates when they are relative.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stream compounding dates, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The compounding date. Type of date is specified in LegPaymentStreamCompoundingDateType(42407).

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the compounding start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding start date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted compounding start date.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the compounding end date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative compounding end date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted compounding end date.

Ccy.description: Non-deliverable settlement reference currency. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

FixngReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the non-deliverable fixing dates are relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FixngPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative non-deliverable fixing date offset.

Ctr.description: The business center calendar used to adjust the payment stream's fixing date for the non-deliverable terms, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. 
                    When LegPaymentStreamNonDeliverableSettlRateSource(40087) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains a value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

Dt.description: The non-deliverable fixing date. Type of date is specified in LegNonDeliverableFixingDateType(40369).

MaxDays.description: The maximum number of days to wait for a quote from the disrupted settlement rate option before proceding to this method.

Survey.description: Indicates whether to request a settlement rate quote from the market.

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. 
                    When LegSettlRateFallbackRateSource(40366) = 3(ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

XID.description: Identifier of this LegPaymentSchedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

XIDRef.description: Reference to payment schedule elsewhere in the message.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on which the value is adjusted, or calculated if a future value notional for certain non-deliverable interest rate swaps (e.g. Brazillian Real (BRL) vs. CETIP Interbank Deposit Rate (CDI)), or the start date of a cashflow payment.

EndDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted end date of a cashflow payment.

Notl.description: The notional value for this step schedule, or amount of a cashflow payment.

Ccy.description: The currency for this step schedule. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Rt.description: The rate value for this step schedule.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Spread.description: The spread value for this step schedule.

RtCcy.description: The currency of the schedule rate. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

RtFctr.description: The number multipled by the derived floating rate of the leg's payment schedule in order to arrive at the payment rate. If omitted, the schedule rate conversion factor is 1.

FixedAmt.description: The explicit payment amount for this step schedule.

FixedCcy.description: The currency of the fixed amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

SettlPxCcy.description: The currency of the schedule settlement period price. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

StepPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the step frequency.

StepVal.description: The explicit amount that the notional changes on each step date. This can be a positive or negative amount.

StepRt.description: The percentage by which the notional changes on each step date. The percentage is either a percentage applied to the initial notional amount or the previous outstanding notional, depending on the value specified in LegPaymentScheduleStepRelativeTo(40395). The percentage can be either positive or negative.

StepOfstRt.description: The explicit amount that the rate changes on each step date. This can be a positive or negative value.

Wt.description: Floating rate observation weight for cashflow payment.

FixngReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the fixing date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

FixngPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative fixing date offset.

FixngDayCnt.description: The number of days over which fixing should take place.

FixngLagPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the fixing lag duration.

FixngFirstObsvtnPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative first observation date offset.

FixngTm.description: The fxing time associated with the step schedule.

FixngTmBizCtr.description:
Business center for determining fixing time. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

IntrmExchDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the interim exchange payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

IntrmExchDtPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative interim exchange date offset.

RefPg.description:
Identifies the reference "page" from the rate source. 
                    For FX, the reference page to the spot rate to be used for the reference FX spot rate. 
                    When RateSource(1446) = 3 (ISDA Settlement Rate Option) this contains the value from the scheme that reflects the terms of the Annex A to the ISDA 1998 FX and Currency Option Definitions. See: http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-rate-option

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment schedule's fixing date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

DayNum.description: The occurrence of the day of week on which fixing takes place.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the payment schedule's interim exchange date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Rt.description: The agreed upon fixed rate for this stub.

FixedAmt.description: A fixed payment amount for the stub.

FixedCcy.description: The currency of the fixed payment amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

NdxPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the floating rate index.

RtMult.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

CapRt.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

FlrRt.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

Ndx2.description: The second stub floating rate index.

Ndx2Period.description: Secondary time unit multiplier for the stub floating rate index curve.

RtMult2.description: A rate multiplier to apply to the second floating rate. The multiplier can be less than or greater than 1 (one). This element should only be included if the multiplier is not equal to 1 (one) for the term of the stream.

Spread2.description: Spread from the second floating rate index.

CapRt2.description: The cap rate, if any, which applies to the second floating rate. The cap rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is capped at a certain level. The cap rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A cap rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

FlrRt2.description: The floor rate, if any, which applies to the second floating rate. The floor rate (strike) is only required where the floating rate on a swap stream is floored at a certain strike level. The floor rate is assumed to be exclusive of any spread and is a per annum rate, expressed as a decimal. A floor rate of 5% would be represented as 0.05.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the stub start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative stub start date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted stub start date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stub start date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the stub end date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative stub end date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted stub end date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the payment stub end date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ppln.description: The name of the oil delivery pipeline.

EntryPnt.description: The point at which the commodity will enter the delivery mechanism or pipeline.

WthdrwlPnt.description: The point at which the commodity product will be withdrawn prior to delivery.

DlvryPnt.description:
The point at which the commodity product will be delivered and received. Value specified should follow market convention appropriate for the commodity product. 
                    For bullion, see http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/bullion-delivery-location for values.

DlvryPntDesc.description: Description of the delivery point identified in LegDeliveryStreamDeliveryPoint(41433).

Cntgncy.description:
Specifies the electricity delivery contingency. See 
                    http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/electricity-transmission-contingency for values.

DlvrAtSrc.description: When this element is specified and set to 'Y', delivery of the coal product is to be at its source.

RiskApprtnmt.description:
Specifies how the parties to the trade apportion responsibility for the delivery of the commodity product. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment for the details of the external code list.

RiskApprtnmtSrc.description:
Specifies the source or legal framework for the risk apportionment. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Risk_Apportionment_Source for the details of the external code list.

Imprtr.description: A party, not necessarily of the trade, who is the Importer of Record for the purposes of paying customs duties and applicable taxes or costs related to importation.

NegtvTlrnc.description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41445). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

PostvTlrnc.description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryStreamToleranceType(41445). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

TotPostvTlrnc.description:
The positive percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. 
                    Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

TotNegtvTlrnc.description:
The negative percent tolerance which applies to the total quantity delivered over all shipment periods. 
                    Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%.).

CnvrsnFctr.description: If the notional quantity is specified in a unit that does not match the unit in which the commodity reference price is quoted, the scaling or conversion factor used to convert the commodity reference price unit into the notional quantity unit should be stated here. If there is no conversion, this field is not intended to be used.

Eqpmt.description: The transportation equipment with which the commodity product will be delivered and received.

RteChrtr.description: Specific delivery route or time charter average. Applicable to commodity freight swaps.

Src.description:
The SCoTA coal cargo origin, mining region, mine(s), mining complex(es), loadout(s) or river dock(s) or other point(s) of origin that seller and buyer agree are acceptable origins for the coal product. For international coal transactions, this is the origin of the coal product. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/commodity-coal-product-source for values.

Desc.description: The delivery cycles during which the oil product will be transported in the pipeline.

EncDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41459) field.

EncDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegDeliveryStreamCycleDesc(41457) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegLeg DeliveryStream(41457) field.

XID.description: Identifier for this instance of delivery schedule for cross referencing elsewhere in the message.

NegtvTlrnc.description: Specifies the negative tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41417). Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

PostvTlrnc.description: Specifies the positive tolerance value. The value may be an absolute quantity or a percentage, as specified in LegDeliveryScheduleToleranceType(41417). Value may exceed agreed upon value. Percentage value is to be expressed relative to "1.0" representing 100% (e.g. a value of "0.0575" represents 5.75%).

Ctry.description: Specifies the country where delivery takes place. Uses ISO 3166 2-character country code.

TZ.description:
Delivery timezone specified as "prevailing" rather than "standard" or "daylight". 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Prevailing_Timezones for code list of applicable prevailing timezones.

TotHrs.description: The sum of the total hours specified in the LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeGrp component.

Start.description: The scheduled start time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41428).

End.description: The scheduled end time for the delivery of the commodity where delivery occurs over specified times. The format of the time value is specified in LegDeliveryScheduleSettlTimeType(41428).

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date of the provision.

Dt.description: The adjusted date of the provision.

TenorPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the leg provision's tenor period.

BrkFeeRt.description: Break fee election rate when the break fee is proportional to the notional. A fee rate of 5% would be represented as "0.05".

anyOf.description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

MultplNotl.description: A notional amount which restricts the amount of notional that can be exercised when partial exercise or multiple exercise is applicable. The integral multiple amount defines a lower limit of notional that can be exercised and also defines a unit multiple of notional that can be exercised, i.e. only integer multiples of this amount can be exercised.

MinNotl.description: The minimum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

MaxNotl.description: The maximum notional amount that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

MinNum.description: The minimum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date.

MaxNum.description: The maximum number of options that can be exercised on a given exercise date. If the number is not specified, it means that the maximum number of options corresponds to the remaining unexercised options.

ExerCnfm.description: Used to indicate whether follow-up confirmation of exercise (written or electronic) is required following telephonic notice by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent.

SettlCcy.description: Specifies the currency of settlement. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

SettlCcy2.description: Specifies the currency of settlement for a cross-currency provision. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Txt.description: Free form text to specify additional information or enumeration description when a standard value does not apply.

EncTxtLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegProvisionText(40472) field.

EncTxt.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegProvisionText(40472) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegProvisionText(40472) field.

Ctr.description: The business center calendar used to adjust the instrument leg's provision's date, e.g. "GBLO". See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Tm.description: A time specified in 24-hour format, e.g. 11am would be represented as 11:00:00. The time of the cash settlement valuation date when the cash settlement amount will be determined according to the cash settlement method if the parties have not otherwise been able to agree to the cash settlement amount.

TmBizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's cash settlement valuation time. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement value date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement value date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted cash settlement value date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the provision's cash settlement valuation date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

ErlstOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the interval to the first (and possibly only) exercise date in the exercise period.

FreqPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for subsequent exercise dates in the exercise period following the earliest exercise date. An interval of 1 day should be used to indicate an American style exercise period.

StartDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

StartDtReltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the option exercise start date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

StartDtOfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option exercise start date offset.

StartDt.description: The adjusted first day of the exercise period for an American style option.

Skip.description: The number of periods in the referenced date schedule that are between each date in the relative date schedule. Thus a skip of 2 would mean that dates are relative to every second date in the referenced schedule. If present this should have a value greater than 1.

FirstDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted first date of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of exercise dates when they are relative.

LastDtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last date of a schedule. This can be used to restrict the range of exercise dates when they are relative.

ErlstTm.description: The earliest time at which notice of exercise can be given by the buyer to the seller (or seller's agent) (i) on the expriation date, in the case of a European style option, (ii) on each bermuda option exercise date and the expiration date, in the case of a Bermuda style option the commencement date to, and including, the expiration date, in the case of an American option.

ErlstTmBizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's earliest time for notice of exercise. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

LtstTm.description: For a Bermuda or American style option, the latest time on an exercise business day (excluding the expiration date) within the exercise period that notice can be given by the buyer to the seller or seller's agent. Notice of exercise given after this time will be deemed to have been given on the next exercise business day.

LtstTmBizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's latest time for notice of exercise. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the instrument leg's provision's option exercise date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: A predetermined option exercise date unadjusted or adjusted depending on LegProvisionOptionExerciseFixedDateType(40497).

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted last day within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only day within the exercise period.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the option expiration date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option expiration date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted last date within an exercise period for an American style option. For a European style option it is the only date within the exercise period.

ExpTm.description: The latest time for exercise on the expiration date.

ExpTmBizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center calendar used with the provision's latest exercise time on expiration date. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the instrument leg's provision's option expiration date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

DtUnadj.description: The unadjusted date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the date relevant to the underlying trade on exercise is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative option relevant underlying date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted date on the underlying set by the exercise of an option. What this date is depends on the option (e.g. in a swaption it is the swap effective date, in an extendible/cancelable provision it is the swap termination date).

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the instrument leg's provision's option underlying date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement payment date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement payment date offset.

DtFirst.description: The first date in range when a settlement date range is provided.

DtLast.description: The last date in range when a settlement date range is provided.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used to adjust the provisional cash settlement payment's termination, or relative termination, date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Dt.description: The cash settlement payment date, unadjusted or adjusted depending on LegProvisionCashSettlPaymentDateType(40521).

RefPg.description: Identifies the reference "page" from the quote source.

ID.description: The party identifier/code for the payment settlement party.
Party sub-identifier, if applicable, for LegProvisionPartyRole(40536).

enum: Registration number (for settlement instructions and confirmations)
Contract linked to commercial or treasury financing for this counterparty
Contract above clearing threshold for this counterparty
anyOf.description: Type of PartySubID(523) value.
Values "4000" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

PrcdntInd.description: Indicates whether the condition precedent bond is applicable. The swap contract is only valid if the bond is issued and if there is any dispute over the terms of fixed stream then the bond terms would be used.

DscrpncyInd.description: Indicates whether the discrepancy clause is applicable.

ID.description: Security identifier of the bond.

enum: Consolidated Tape Association (CTA) Symbol (SIAC CTS/CQS line format)
anyOf.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID(48) value.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Desc.description: Description of the bond.

EncDescLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41321) field.

EncDesc.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41319) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegAdditionalTermBondDesc(41319) field.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency the bond value is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

EncIssrLen.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedLegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41325) field.

EncIssr.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the LegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41323) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the LegAdditionalTermBondIssuer(41323) field.

CpnRt.description: Coupon rate of the bond. See also CouponRate(223).

MatDt.description: The maturity date of the bond.

Par.description: The par value of the bond.

CurTotAmt.description: Total issued amount of the bond.

CpnPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the frequency of the bond's coupon payment.

anyOf.description: The day count convention used in interest calculations for a bond or an interest bearing security. Absence of this field for a bond or an interest bearing security transaction implies a "flat" trade, i.e. no accrued interest determined at time of the transaction.
Values "100" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

Notl.description: The notional amount of protection coverage.

Ccy.description: The currency of LegProtectionTermNotional(41618). Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Seller.description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. LegProtectionTermSellerNotifies(41620)=Y indicates that the seller notifies.

Buyer.description: The notifying party is the party that notifies the other party when a credit event has occurred by means of a credit event notice. If more than one party is referenced as being the notifying party then either party may notify the other of a credit event occurring. LegProtectionTermBuyerNotifies(41621)=Y indicates that the buyer notifies.

BizCtr.description:
When used, the business center indicates the local time of the business center that replaces the Greenwich Mean Time in Section 3.3 of the 2003 ISDA Credit Derivatives Definitions. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

StdSrcs.description: Indicates whether ISDA defined Standard Public Sources are applicable (LegProtectionTermStandardSources(41623)=Y) or not.

MinSrcs.description: The minimum number of the specified public information sources that must publish information that reasonably confirms that a credit event has occurred. The market convention is two.

XID.description: A named string value referenced from UnderlyingProtectionTermXIDRef(41314).

Src.description: A newspaper or electronic news service that may publish relevant information used in the determination of whether or not a credit event has occurred.

Typ.description:
Specifies the type of credit event applicable to the protection terms. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for code list of applicable event types.

Val.description: Specifies the protection term event value appropriate to LegProtectionTermEventType(41626). See http:///www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Event_Types for applicable event type values.

Ccy.description: Applicable currency if the event value is an amount. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

Period.description: Time unit multiplier for protection term events.

RtSrc.description: Rate source for events that specify a rate source, e.g. floating rate interest shortfall.

Typ.description:
Specifies the type of obligation applicable to the protection terms. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for code list of applicable obligation types.

Val.description: The value associated with the protection term obligation specified in LegProtectionTermObligationType(41636). See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Protection_Term_Obligation_Types for applicable obligation type values.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlAmount(41357) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

BizDayOfst.description: The number of business days after settlement conditions have been satisfied, when the calculation agent is to obtain a price quotation on the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement.

SbsqntBizDayOfst.description: The number of business days between successive valuation dates when multiple valuation dates are applicable for cash settlement.

NumValDts.description: Where multiple valuation dates are specified as being applicable for cash settlement, this element specifies the number of applicable valuation dates.

BizCtr.description:
Identifies the business center calendar used at valuation time for cash settlement purposes e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

QteAmt.description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the upper limit to the outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount equal to floating rate payer calculation amount.

QteCcy.description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlQuoteAmount(41352) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

MinQteAmt.description: When determining the cash settlement amount, if weighted average price quotes are to be obtained for the reference obligation, this is the minimum intended threshold amount of outstanding principal balance of the reference obligation for which the quote should be obtained. If not specified, the ISDA definitions provide for a fallback amount of the lower of either USD1,000,000 (or its equivalent in the relevant obligation currency) or the (minimum) quoted amount.

MinQteCcy.description: Specifies the currency the LegCashSettlQuoteMinimumAmount(41354) is denominated in. Uses ISO 4217 Currency Code.

PxSrc.description:
The source from which the settlement price is to be obtained. 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/settlement-price-source for values.

BizDays.description: The number of business days used in the determination of the cash settlement payment date.

Amt.description: The amount paid between the trade parties, seller to the buyer, for cash settlement on the cash settlement date.

RcvryFctr.description: Used for fixed recovery, this specifies the recovery level as determined at contract inception, to be applied in the event of a default. The factor is used to calculate the amount paid by the seller to the buyer for cash settlement on the cash settlement date. The amount calculated is (1 - LegCashSettlRecoveryFactor(41358)) x floating rate payer calculation amount. The currency is derived from the floating rate payer calculation amount.

FixedInd.description: Indicates whether fixed settlement is applicable or not applicable in a recovery lock.

AcrdIntInd.description:
Indicates whether accrued interest is included or not in the value provided in LegCashSettlAmount(41357). 
                    For cash settlement this specifies whether quotations should be obtained inclusive or not of accrued interest. 
                    For physical settlement this specifies whether the buyer should deliver the obligation with an outstanding principal balance that includes or excludes accrued interest.

XID.description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef(41315).

Dlr.description: Identifies the dealer from whom price quotations for the reference obligation are obtained for the purpose of cash settlement valuation calculation.

Reltv.description:
Specifies the anchor date when the cash settlement date is relative to an anchor date. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Relative_To_Date for values.

OfstPeriod.description: Time unit multiplier for the relative cash settlement date offset.

Dt.description: The adjusted cash settlement date.

Ctr.description:
The business center calendar used for date adjustment of the cash settlement unadjusted or relative date, e.g. "GBLO". 
                    See http://www.fpml.org/coding-scheme/business-center for standard 4-character code values.

Ccy.description: Specifies the currency of physical settlement. Uses ISO 4217 currency codes.

BizDays.description: The number of business days used in the determination of physical settlement. Its precise meaning depends on the context in which this is used.

MaxBizDays.description: A maximum number of business days. Its precise meaning depends on the context in which this element is used. Intended to be used to limit a particular ISDA fallback provision.

XID.description: A named string value referenced by UnderlyingSettlTermXIDRef(41315).

Typ.description:
Specifies the type of delivery obligation applicable for physical settlement. 
                    See http://www.fixptradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for code list for applicable deliverable obligation types.

Val.description:
Physical settlement delivery obligation value appropriate to LegPhysicalSettlDeliverableObligationType(41605). 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Deliverable_Obligation_Types for code list for applicable deliverable obligation types.

Typ.description:
Identifies the type of extraordinary or disruptive event applicable to the reference entity. 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

Val.description:
The extraordinary or disruptive event value appropriate to LegExtraordinaryEventType(42389). 
                    See http://www.fixtradingcommunity.org/codelists#Extraordinary_Event_Type for code list of extraordinary event types and values.

StipVal.description:
For Fixed Income, value of stipulation. 
                    See StipulationValue (234) for description and valid values

AllocAcct.description:
Allocation Account for the leg 
                    See AllocAccount (79) for description and valid values.

IndAllocID.description:
Reference for the individual allocation ticket 
                    See IndividualAllocID (467) for description and valid values.

AllocQty.description:
Leg allocation quantity. 
                    See AllocQty (80) for description and valid values.

AllocSettlCcy.description: Identifies settlement currency for the leg level allocation.

CstdlLotID.description: An opaque identifier used to communicate the custodianâ€™s identifier for the lot. It is expected that this information would be provided by the custodian as part of a reconciliation process that occurs before trading.

VSPDt.description: The effective acquisition date of the lot that would be used for gain-loss trade lot reporting. The versus purchase date used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.

VSPPx.description: The versus purchase price used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.The value should be calculated based on current cost basis / quantity held.

CurCostBasis.description: The amount that the current shares are worth. If this lot was liquidated, the total gain/loss for a trade is equal to the trade amount minus the current cost basis.

ID.description:
PartyID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. 
                    Same values as PartyID (448)

PartySubID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group. 
                    Same values as PartySubID (523)

Values "4000" and above are reserved for bilaterally agreed upon user defined enumerations.

PartyID value within a nested repeating group. 
                    Same values as PartyID (448)

                    Same values as PartySubID (523)
